== Meatloaf ==

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Place in a large #pot{} with a large pinch of @salt{} and enough water to cover. Bring to a boil. Cook about ~{15%minutes}, until fork-tender. Reserve ½ cup cooking liquid, then drain.

Meanwhile, halve and core 1 @Granny Smith Apple{1}. Using a #box grater{}, grate the cored apple into a large #bowl{}. Peel and grate the @shallots{2} into the same bowl. Add the @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Ground Pork{20%ounce}, and @Dried Rosemary{1%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{1 1/2%teaspoons}(kosher salt) and @pepper{}. Thoroughly combine with your hands, and form into four loaves, approximately 1 1/2 inches thick.

Place the loaves onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake about ~{18-22%minutes}, or until cooked through.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Once the potatoes have been drained, heat @Butter{2%tablespoons} in the same pot. Return the potatoes to the pot along with the @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}. Mash with a #fork{} or #potato masher{} until smooth, adding as much cooking liquid as needed for a creamy consistency. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover and set aside.

== Green Salad ==

Thinly slice the @Celery{2} on a diagonal. Core and thinly slice the remaining @Granny Smith Apple{1}. Toss the apple slices, celery, and @Mixed Greens{4%ounce} in a large bowl with a large drizzle of @Balsamic Vinegar{4%tablespoon} and @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Nothing screams fall more than apples, and nothing pairs better with apples than pork. For this recipe, our chefs chose the Granny Smith variety for its hard, crisp, and slightly tart flesh. When it's shredded and mixed with pork, the result is a deliciously juicy meatloaf your kids will love.

== To Serve ==

Serve the pork and apple meatloaf on a bed of creamy mashed potatoes with the green salad on the side. Enjoy!